I would not suggest using google doc, as you have to go through the hassle of signing into google whenever you want to write something, and considering that it's an always-online google product, it probably spies on you. Microsoft word is too expensive, so I wouldn't use that either.
I personally suggest you create an unlisted pastebin and editing it whenever you want to work on your project, and then setting it to public when it's finished. Whenever the internet goes out or you don't feel like logging into pastebin, notepad makes for a good alternative. Something that I recently found out was that you can actually click and drag to highlight what you wrote in notepad, right click on the words, and click "copy". Then go to click on your pastebin and right click again, this time clicking the "paste" button, which instantly transports everything that you wrote in notepad to the pastebin without you having to copy it down word for word. Knowing this trick has saved me countless hours, and I guarantee it will come in handy for you as well.
